        "\n",
        "# Advantages & Disadvantages of CRD\n",
        "\n",
        ":::: {.columns}\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"48%\"}\n",
        "::: {.callout-tip icon=false}\n",
        "## Advantages\n",
        "‚Ä¢ Simple to design and analyze  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Flexible in number of treatments and replications  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Maximum degrees of freedom for error term  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Missing data doesn't complicate analysis significantly  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Easy to understand and implement\n",
        ":::\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.column width=\"48%\"}\n",
        "::: {.callout-warning icon=false}\n",
        "## Disadvantages\n",
        "‚Ä¢ Requires homogeneous experimental conditions  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Less precise than blocking designs when heterogeneity exists  \n",
        "‚Ä¢ Can lead to larger experimental error if conditions are not uniform\n",
        ":::\n",
        ":::\n",
        "\n",
        "::::\n",
